From 69140fdcb29613f5f6dd081044c9b4622a0e5d3b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: melnoff <melnoff360@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 19:00:33 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(ui): VLESS subscription proxy type, persistence, refresh
 wiring
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds the user-facing layer that turns a Happ:// or https:// VLESS
subscription URL into a working proxy. Builds on patches 09 and 10.

  * ProxyData gains Type::VlessSubscription. host stores the
    subscription URL (port/user/password unused). status() accepts
    happ://, http(s):// schemes. forUse() pulls the cached server
    list from SubscriptionCache and hands it to
    VlessBridge::ensureRunningSubscription so sing-box can urltest
    internally. ToNetworkProxy and core_settings_proxy serialization
    case 5 follow.

  * SubscriptionCache (new) — singleton, keyed by subscription URL,
    stored as JSON in the app data dir (sovagram_subscriptions.json).
    Servers persist as vless:// strings via BuildVlessUrl/ParseVlessUrl
    so a subscription proxy works at the next launch without the user
    re-opening the edit dialog.

  * connection_box: drops the Phase-2A subscription placeholder fields
    (_vlessSub*) from the single-server VLESS form, adds a separate
    "VLESS SUB" radio with its own credentials wrap. The form has the
    subscription URL field, a "Refresh now" link button that drives a
    SubscriptionFetcher (writes the cache, restarts the sidecar via
    VlessBridge::stopSubscription), a status line, and a server names
    list. On open, the form prefills cached names if any.

  * setupTypes/setupControls/handleType/collectData and the
    type→string switch updated for the new type. SocketAddress is
    hidden for both Vless variants.
